\[\frac{AC}{AD} = \frac{\sin(\angle CAD)}{\sin(\angle ADC)} = \frac{\sin(2x)}{\sin(90^\circ - 3x)} = \frac{\cos(x)}{\cos(3x)}.\]
Also,
\[\frac{CD}{BD} = \frac{AC \cdot \sin(\angle ACD)}{AB \cdot \sin(\angle ABD)} = \frac{AC \cdot \sin(x)}{AB \cdot \sin(2x)} = \frac{AC}{2AB \cdot \cos(x)}.\]
From the Law of Sines on triangle $ABC$, we have
\[\frac{AC}{\sin(\angle ABC)} = \frac{BC}{\sin(\angle BAC)},\]
so
\[\frac{BC}{AC} = \frac{\sin(\angle BAC)}{\sin(\angle ABC)} = \cos(3x).\]
Since $\triangle ABD$ is a right triangle, $\frac{BD}{AB} = \cos(x)$. Therefore,
\[\frac{CD}{BD} = \frac{AC}{2AB \cdot \cos(x)} = \frac{2}{BC \cdot \cos(x)} = \frac{2}{\frac{AC}{\cos(3x)} \cdot \cos(x)} = \frac{2 \cos(3x)}{\frac{2}{3} \cos(x)} = \frac{3 \cos(3x)}{\cos(x)} = \boxed{9}.\]```

